element.name: M is for Magnet by Hezekiah, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

element.long-description: In the grounds of the Belfield campus of NUI - near a building which was once part of Trinity College, but was transported block by block in the 1970's to its current location. This building was constructed especially to house experiments related to magnetism and there is no magnetic material whatsoever used in its construction.

ul.li:
2010-06-10T19:00:00Z : Found it by Mie G
During a break in a very interesting conference on UCD - we had some good fresh irish air - and a catch!
Mie and Birthe

2010-05-20T19:00:00Z : Found it by Fitzet
For a few minutes I thought I was going to have to log the Log of Shame - first ever DNF on a cache [:I].
Then, through luck or whatever, I spotted the cache lying on the ground, a couple of feet from it's intended location. I may even have dislodged it myself.
Anyway, it's now back in place, with some light camoflague.
Log is damp
SL TFTC

2007-09-13T07:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
Walked here from F is for Fen. Finally located the spot and there were two security-muggles hanging around. We decided to wait on the grass for a while, but when it was clear that they were going nowhere I decided being obvious was the best ploy. Showed the cache and the GPS but they really didn't seem interested.
